description: Number of noncommutative SL(2,C)-invariants of degree n in 5 variables.
references: N. J. A. Sloane and Simon Plouffe, The Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences, Academic Press, 1995 (includes this sequence).
links: Gert Almkvist, Warren Dicks, Edward Formanek, Hilbert series of fixed free algebras and noncommutative classical invariant theory, J. Algebra 93 (1985), no. 1, 189-214.
Eliahu Cohen, Tobias Hansen, Nissan Itzhaki, From Entanglement Witness to Generalized Catalan Numbers, arXiv:1511.06623 [quant-ph], 2015.
maple: F := (t^2+3*t+1)/((t+1)*(4*t+1)^(1/2)); G := t/(t^2+3*t+1); Ginv := RootOf(numer(G-x),t);  ogf := series(eval(F,t=Ginv),x=0,20); # _Mark van Hoeij_, Oct 30 2011
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, _Mira Bernstein_
